fields.title: Software Engineer I
fields.requirements:
BA/BS in Computer Science or Computer Engineering preferred, Programming Certificate, or similar training/experience
Knowledge of one or more of the following Java or C# or any other Object Oriented programming language, Angular or React, JavaScript, CSS, HTML
Have a systematic problem-solving approach coupled with effective communication skills
Enjoy working on a team where you constantly learn, experiment, and iterate quickly
fields.description:
Explore and work with cutting-edge technologies and a tremendously large (and fantastically rich) data set.
Design, develop and deploy different services that scale, are highly available, and are easy to extend.
Solve interesting and challenging problems alongside a great team of deeply technical engineers.
Collaborate with and across Agile teams to design, develop, test, implement, and support technical solutions in full-stack development tools and technologies

fields.title: Associate Software Engineer
fields.requirements:
*The desire to put engineering skills and techniques to work for customers
*Experience with or an interest to use technologies ranging from Node.js, Postgres, SQL, and other technologies to support data cleaning, transaction management, and database management.
*Ownership mentality- taking pride in the work you do
fields.description: As an Associate Engineer on the Data Support Services Team, you will help advance this company's product data management and scientific data enrichment systems. These systems prepare materials to allow scientists to search millions of data rich records when ordering equipment, chemicals and lab consumables and provide suppliers with rich analytics about purchased products. You are a fit for the role if you enjoy working on end-to-end solutions in a collaborative environment. Ideally you have experience with e-commerce platforms, database systems and are comfortable working in a dynamic environment. You are thoughtful in your approach to design and engineer solutions that meet business demands while optimizing for system health, security and long-term maintenance.

fields.title: Software Engineer
fields.requirements:
Bachelor’s degree in Engineering related discipline. (i.e. Computer Science, Mathematics, Electrical Engineering, etc.).
Experience with Object Oriented Programming.
Hands-on problem solver with excellent software design and implementation skills.
Able to work in a fast-paced environment and support unscheduled events.
Understand source control (git preferred).
Comfortable with asynchronous or multithread programming, inter-process communication, and automated software testing.
Comfortable writing software in a managed language such as C# or Java.
Testing and debugging experience is required while experience developing automated tests is preferred.
Experience with a data analytics tools (plotting libraries, regex, ELK) is a plus.
Experience with Linux and its commands is a plus.
fields.description:
Design and develop real-time distributed software to communicate with and manage data for fleets of mobile robots and other warehouse automation hardware.
Play a hands-on role as part of an engineering team developing solutions for planning and scheduling the fleet of mobile robots.
Demonstrate passion about building high quality software, love solving problems and facing new challenges. 
Be a proactive communicator who enjoys working closely with creative and technical peers. 
Work in a dynamic Agile/Scrum based environment.

fields.title: Application Developer
fields.requirements:
1-8 years of Industry Software Development Experience.
Programming experience with an Object Oriented or Functional programming language.
Understanding of web programming
C#/.NET, and SQL Server a plus.
Physical Requirements: None.
fields.description:
Working as a member of a development team under the guidance and direction of a Senior Application Developer to create custom enterprise applications for customers across SCA.
Having a passion to learn and grow both technically and professionally.
Able to lead the technical side of small development projects.
Ensuring there is a focus on delivering rich user experiences that meets user’s needs.
Being accountable for their own development delivery commitments and quality.
Building influence within the development team to help with future technology and methodology decisions.

fields.title: Associate Software Engineer
fields.requirements:
Make meaningful contributions to Labviva's data capture and preparation systems aiding its evolution and advancement, while gaining skills in key technologies.
Balance adding new functionality with reliability, maintenance, performance and security objectives under an agile framework.
Contribute to an engineering culture of shipping great products.
Build integrations with third party APIs for handling marketplace order transactions.
Approach the role with an ownership mentality, taking pride in the services we produce.
Support and learn from other members of the team fostering a culture of inclusiveness and respect.

fields.title: Software Engineer
fields.benefits: Stock options, Sign-On Bonus, Referral Bonus
fields.requirements:
Experience across multiple courses where writing software is a primary element.
Hands-on experience with Git in a shared repository.
Comfort in picking up new languages and technologies quickly.
Exposure to object-oriented languages (e.g. Java, C#).
Collaborative, team-based implementation, either in an internship or project setting.
Experience writing unit tests.
fields.description:
You will be developing systems and APIs that power a rich set of applications used by a large and passionate group of users every day.
Care about agility as much as you care about scalability. We roll out products very quickly and are looking for a team that can pivot at a moment’s notice.
Triage and debug software application issues.
Work with modern technologies on scalable, reliable systems that people use in a 24/7 sports betting market.
Contribute to production code immediately.
